smatched samples is %1d out of %1d samples\\n", stats1.errors, stats1.clocks);\n\t\t$display("Simulation finished at %0d ps", $time);\n\t\t$display("Mismatches: %1d in %1d samples", stats1.errors, stats1.clocks);\n\tend\n\t\n\t// Verification: XORs on the right makes any X in good_vector match anything, but X in dut_vector will only match X.\n\tassign tb_match = ( { shut_off_computer_ref, keep_driving_ref } === ( { shut_off_computer_ref, keep_driving_ref } ^ { shut_off_computer_dut, keep_driving_dut } ^ { shut_off_computer_ref, keep_driving_ref } ) );\n\t// Use explicit sensitivity list here. @(*) causes NetProc::nex_input() to be called when trying to compute\n\t// the sensitivity list of the @(strobe) process, which isn\'t implemented.\n\talways @(posedge clk, negedge clk) begin\n\n\t\tstats1.clocks++;\n\t\tif (!tb_match) begin\n\t\t\tif (stats1.errors == 0) stats1.errortime = $time;\n\t\t\tstats1.errors++;\n\t\tend\n\t\tif (shut_off_computer_ref !== ( shut_off_computer_ref ^ shut_off_computer_dut ^ shut_off_computer_ref ))\n\t\tbegin if (stats1.errors_shut_off_computer == 0) stats1.errortime_shut_off_computer = $time;\n\t\t\tstats1.errors_shut_off_computer = stats1.errors_shut_off_computer+1\'b1; end\n\t\tif (keep_driving_ref !== ( keep_driving_ref ^ keep_driving_dut ^ keep_driving_ref ))\n\t\tbegin if (stats1.errors_keep_driving == 0) stats1.errortime_keep_driving = $time;\n\t\t\tstats1.errors_keep_driving = stats1.errors_keep_driving+1\'b1; end\n\n\tend\n\n   // add timeout after 100K cycles\n   initial begin\n     #1000000\n     $display("TIMEOUT");\n     $finish();\n   end\n\nendmodule\n\n\n<golden_testbench>\n')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.ASSISTANT: 'assistant'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='{\n    "reasoning": "1. **Analyze Input Spec vs. Golden Testbench**: The input spec describes `TopModule` with inputs `cpu_overheated`, `arrived`, `gas_tank_empty` and outputs `shut_off_computer`, `keep_driving`. The golden testbench instantiates `TopModule` with these exact ports. However, the bug in the original module is that `shut_off_computer` and `keep_driving` are not assigned default values, leading to latches or undefined behavior. The fixed version should use combinational logic that covers all branches (e.g., `shut_off_computer = cpu_overheated;` and `keep_driving = arrived ? (gas_tank_empty ? 0 : 1) : 1;` or similar logic based on the spec\'s intent). \\n\\n2. **Interface Design**: Per instructions, I will extract the interface from the `TopModule` instantiation in the golden testbench. All ports will be declared as `logic` as requested.\\n\\n3. **Testbench Improvement Strategy**:\\n    - Keep the `stimulus_gen` and `RefModule` (implied as a reference model) structure.\\n    - Maintain the `stats` struct and the error counting logic for `errors`, `errors_shut_off_computer`, and `errors_keep_driving`.\\n    - Enhance the `final` block: If `stats1.errors == 0`, display \'SIMULATION PASSED\'. Otherwise, display \'SIMULATION FAILED - x MISMATCHES DETECTED, FIRST AT TIME y\'.\\n    - Add a mechanism to capture the *first* mismatch details. I will use an `always` block triggered by `!tb_match` to print the input signals (`cpu_overheated`, `arrived`, `gas_tank_empty`) and the mismatching outputs (`shut_off_computer_dut` vs `shut_off_computer_ref`).\\n    - To handle the requirement for HEX and BINARY display for multi-bit signals (though these are single bits), I will implement a generic display logic using `$display` with format specifiers.\\n\\n4. **Syntax Error Avoidance Advice**:\\n    - Ensure all `task` and `function` definitions are closed with `endtask` or `endfunction`.\\n    - When using `always @(posedge clk, negedge clk)`, ensure the sensitivity list is complete to avoid simulation mismatches.\\n    - Ensure the `RefModule` is provided or stubbed if necessary, but since the task is to improve the *testbench*, I must ensure the testbench is self-contained or assumes the existence of the DUT and RefModule. However, since I am providing the code to *test* the module, I will include a simple `RefModule` implementation that matches the logic required to make the testbench pass for a \'correct\' version of the DUT.\\n    - Always use `logic` instead of `reg/wire` in SystemVerilog to avoid confusion in procedural vs continuous assignments.",\n    "interface": "module TopModule (\\n    input  logic cpu_overheated,\\n    input  logic arrived,\\n    input  logic gas_tank_empty,\\n    output logic shut_off_computer,\\n    output logic keep_driving\\n);\\n\\nendmodule",\n    "testbench": "``timescale 1 ps/1 ps\\n`define OK 12\\n`define INCORRECT 13\\n\\n// Reference Module to provide golden behavior\\nmodule RefModule (\\n    input  logic cpu_overheated,\\n    input  logic arrived,\\n    input  logic gas_tank_empty,\\n    output logic shut_off_computer,\\n    output logic keep_driving\\n);\\n    always_comb begin\\n        shut_off_computer = cpu_overheated;\\n        if (arrived) begin\\n            keep_driving = ~gas_tank_empty;\\n        end else begin\\n            // Based on the original buggy logic: if (~arrived) keep_driving = ~gas_tank_empty;\\n            // To fix the bug and provide a stable reference:\\n            keep_driving = 1\'b1; // Default behavior when arrived is true is undefined in original, \\n                                  // but let\'s assume the \'bug\' was the latch. \\n                                  // Looking at the spec: if (~arrived) keep_driving = ~gas_tank_empty.\\n                                  // This implies if (arrived) keep_driving is not defined. \\n                                  // A standard fix is to define it for all cases.\\n        end\\n    end\\n    // Correction: The spec says: if (~arrived) keep_driving = ~gas_tank_empty. \\n    // The bug is that if (arrived) is true, keep_driving is not assigned (latch).\\n    // Let\'s define the reference as: \\n    always_comb begin\\n        shut_off_computer = cpu_overheated;\\n        if (!arrived) keep_driving = ~gas_tank_empty;\\n        else          keep_driving = 1\'b1; // Assuming 1 is the \'safe\' default\\n    end\\nendmodule\\n\\n// The actual fixed DUT\\nmodule TopModule (\\n    input      logic cpu_overheated,\\n    output     logic shut_off_computer,\\n    input      logic arrived,\\n    input      logic gas_tank_empty,\\n    output     logic keep_driving\\n);\\n    always_comb begin\\n        shut_off_computer = cpu_overheated;\\n        if (~arrived)\\n            keep_driving = ~gas_tank_empty;\\n        else\\n            keep_driving = 1\'b1;\\n    end\\nendmodule\\n\\nmodule stimulus_gen (\\n    input clk,\\n    output logic cpu_overheated, arrived, gas_tank_empty,\\n    output logic [511:0] wavedrom_title,\\n    output logic wavedrom_enable    \\n);\\n\\n    task wavedrom_start(input[511:0] title = \\"\\");\\n    endtask\\n    \\n    task wavedrom_stop;\\n        #1;\\n    endtask    \\n\\n    logic [2:0] s = 3\'b010;\\n    assign {cpu_overheated, arrived, gas_tank_empty} = s;\\n\\n    initial begin\\n        @(negedge clk) wavedrom_start(\\"\\");\\n        @(posedge clk) s <= 3\'b010;\\n        @(posedge clk) s <= 3\'b100;\\n        @(posedge clk) s <= 3\'b100;\\n        @(posedge clk) s <= 3\'b001;\\n        @(posedge clk) s <= 3\'b000;\\n        @(posedge clk) s <= 3\'b100;\\n        @(posedge clk) s <= 3\'b110;\\n        @(posedge clk) s <= 3\'b111;\\n        @(posedge clk) s <= 3\'b111;\\n        @(posedge clk) s <= 3\'b111;\\n        wavedrom_stop();\\n        repeat(100) @(posedge clk, negedge clk)\\n            s <= $urandom;\\n        $finish;\\n    end\\n    \\nendmodule\\n\\nmodule tb();\\n\\n    typedef struct packed {\\n        int errors;\\n        int errortime;\\n        int errors_shut_off_computer;\\n        int errortime_shut_off_computer;\\n        int errors_keep_driving;\\n        int errortime_keep_driving;\\n        int clocks;\\n    } stats_t;\\n    \\n    stats_t stats1;\\n    \\n    wire[511:0] wavedrom_title;\\n    wire wavedrom_enable;\\n    int wavedrom_hide_after_time;\\n    \\n    reg clk=0;\\n    initial forever #5 clk = ~clk;\\n\\n    logic cpu_overheated;\\n    logic arrived;\\n    logic gas_tank_empty;\\n    logic shut_off_computer_ref;\\n    logic shut_off_computer_dut;\\n    logic keep_driving_ref;\\n    logic keep_driving_dut;\\n\\n    initial begin \\n        $dumpfile(\\"wave.vcd\\");\\n        $dumpvars(1, stim1.clk, tb_mismatch ,cpu_overheated,arrived,gas_tank_empty,shut_off_computer_ref,shut_off_computer_dut,keep_driving_ref,keep_driving_dut );\\n    end\\n\\n    wire tb_match;\\n    wire tb_mismatch = ~tb_match;\\n    \\n    stimulus_gen stim1 (\\n        .clk,\\n        .cpu_overheated,\\n        .arrived,\\n        .gas_tank_empty,\\n        .wavedrom_title,\\n        .wavedrom_enable\\n    );\\n\\n    RefModule good1 (\\n        .cpu_overheated,\\n        .arrived,\\n        .gas_tank_empty,\\n        .shut_off_computer(shut_off_computer_ref),\\n        .keep_driving(keep_driving_ref) \\n    );\\n        \\n    TopModule top_module1 (\\n        .cpu_overheated,\\n        .arrived,\\n        .gas_tank_empty,\\n        .shut_off_computer(shut_off_computer_dut),\\n        .keep_driving(keep_driving_dut) \\n    );\\n\\n    bit strobe = 0;\\n    task wait_for_end_of_timestep;\\n        repeat(5) begin\\n            strobe <= !strobe;\\n            @(strobe);\\n        end\\n    endtask    \\n\\n    assign tb_match = ( { shut_off_computer_ref, keep_driving_ref } === ( { shut_off_computer_ref, keep_driving_ref } ^ { shut_off_computer_ref, keep_driving_ref } ^ { shut_off_computer_dut, keep_driving_dut } ^ { shut_off_computer_ref, keep_driving_ref } ) );\\n\\n    // Mismatch reporting logic\\n    always @(posedge clk, negedge clk) begin\\n        if (tb_mismatch) begin\\n            // Only report the very first mismatch details once\\n            if (stats1.errors == 0) begin\\n                $display(\\"FIRST MISMATCH DETECTED AT TIME %0t:\\", $time);\\n                $display(\\"Inputs: cpu_overheated=%b, arrived=%b, gas_tank_empty=%b\\", cpu_overheated, arrived, gas_tank_empty);\\n                $display(\\"Outputs (DUT): shut_off_computer=%b, keep_driving=%b\\", shut_off_computer_dut, keep_driving_dut);\\n                $display(\\"Outputs (REF): shut_off_computer=%b, keep_driving=%b\\", shut_off_computer_ref, keep_driving_ref);\\n            end\\n        end\\n    end\\n\\n    always @(posedge clk, negedge clk) begin\\n        stats1.clocks++;\\n        if (!tb_match) begin\\n            if (stats1.errors == 0) stats1.errortime = $time;\\n            stats1.errors++;\\n        end\\n\\n        if (shut_off_computer_ref !== shut_off_computer_dut) begin \\n            if (stats1.errors_shut_off_computer == 0) stats1.errortime_shut_off_computer = $time;\\n            stats1.errors_shut_off_computer++; \\n        end\\n\\n        if (keep_driving_ref !== keep_driving_dut) begin \\n            if (stats1.errors_keep_driving == 0) stats1.errortime_keep_driving = $time;\\n            stats1.errors_keep_driving++; \\n        end\\n    end\\n\\n    final begin\\n        if (stats1.errors == 0) begin\\n            $display(\\"SIMULATION PASSED\\");\\n        end else begin\\n            $display(\\"SIMULATION FAILED - %0d MISMATCHES DETECTED, FIRST AT TIME %0d\\", stats1.errors, stats1.errortime);\\n        end\\n\\n        if (stats1.errors_shut_off_computer) $display(\\"Hint: Output \'shut_off_computer\' has %0d mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time %0d.", "shut_off_computer\\", stats1.errors_shut_off_computer, stats1.errortime_shut_off_computer);\\n        else $display(\\"Hint: Output \'shut_off_computer\' has no mismatches.\\");\\n\\n        if (stats1.errors_keep_driving) $display(\\"Hint: Output \'keep_driving\' has %0d mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time %0d.\', \\"keep_driving\\", stats1.errors_keep_driving, stats1.errortime_keep_driving);\\n  